  "texts": [
    "Pedraza et al. (2017) introduce an innovative application of CNNs for the classification of diatom species, utilizing a dataset of 160,000 images across 80 species.",
    "They present a modified AlexNet architecture, optimized for diatom classification by using multiple data augmentation techniques, such as rotations and normalization, to improve model robustness across diverse imaging conditions.",
    "Key architectural modifications include the introduction of dropout layers and the use of histogram matching for dataset normalization, enhancing the model's generalization and reducing overfitting.",
    "However, The fixed kernel size employed throughout the network may limit the model's adaptability to different feature scales inherent in varied diatom morphologies.",
    "Wang et al. (2022) introduce a TL based DL solution for identifying specific taxa of rare Cambrian microfossils that sample a broad range of clades."
